@startuml iam-service-account-management
' Requirements: L1-SEC-001, L2-SEC-001
' Source: docs/specs/security/L1.md, docs/specs/security/L2.md
title IAM Service Account Resource Operations (list, create, update)
autonumber

actor "Administrator" as ADM
participant "HTTP API" as API
participant "Auth Middleware" as MW
participant "IAM Handler" as IAM
participant "Token Service" as TOK
database "IAM Store" as DB

note over ADM, DB
  L2-SEC-001: GIVEN an authenticated administrator
  WHEN IAM list/create/update methods are called
  THEN responses follow documented IAM resource structures.
  Service accounts are non-human identities for tooling and pipelines.
end note

== List service accounts ==
ADM -> API : GET /api/iam/service-accounts
activate API
API -> MW : Authenticate(request)
activate MW
MW --> API : principal (administrator)
deactivate MW
API -> IAM : ListServiceAccountsQuery
activate IAM
IAM -> DB : select service account records
activate DB
DB --> IAM : service account rows
deactivate DB
IAM --> API : ListServiceAccountsResponse (documented resource structure)
deactivate IAM
API --> ADM : 200 OK { serviceAccounts: [ { name, displayName, active } ] }
deactivate API

== Create service account ==
ADM -> API : POST /api/iam/service-accounts { name, displayName }
activate API
API -> MW : Authenticate(request)
activate MW
MW --> API : principal (administrator)
deactivate MW
API -> IAM : CreateServiceAccountCommand
activate IAM
IAM -> IAM : validate name uniqueness
IAM -> TOK : GenerateClientCredential(serviceAccount)
activate TOK
TOK --> IAM : client id + client secret (returned once)
deactivate TOK
IAM -> DB : insert service account record (secret stored hashed)
activate DB
DB --> IAM : stored
deactivate DB
IAM --> API : ServiceAccountResource + one-time credential
deactivate IAM
API --> ADM : 201 Created { serviceAccount, clientId, clientSecret }
deactivate API

== Update service account (activate/deactivate, roles) ==
ADM -> API : PATCH /api/iam/service-accounts/{name} { active, roles }
activate API
API -> MW : Authenticate(request)
activate MW
MW --> API : principal (administrator)
deactivate MW
API -> IAM : UpdateServiceAccountCommand
activate IAM
IAM -> DB : load service account record
activate DB
DB --> IAM : service account row
deactivate DB
IAM -> IAM : apply changes, validate role references
IAM -> DB : persist updated record
activate DB
DB --> IAM : stored
deactivate DB
IAM --> API : ServiceAccountResource (updated)
deactivate IAM
API --> ADM : 200 OK { serviceAccount }
deactivate API
@enduml
